node.text:
Understanding your Soul purpose is a starting point to understand how to feel fully expanded and inspired within ourselves. Your Soul Purpose is a core part of our true self that we can integrate into every area of life. A life with a deep understanding of our Soul Purpose lends itself to a life that is lived in flow. So you know that you are doing what you are meant to be doing; you are in the right place at the right time, living by your own internal compass and set of values. You are at peace with your internal and external realities.

Each time you discover what lights you up inside, there is something even greater beyond that. But going into an inquiry is a great way to consider what might be limiting you. Really, the sky is the limit. 

Follow @DavidSamuelStraus to learn how to discover your soul's purpose!🙏

How to solve a problem with @DavidSamuelStraus 🧐

Imagine a problem, a concern, or hurdle you currently have in your life.  That problem concern or hurdle is equal to your current level of awareness (consciousness) as it relates to that problem.  When we know how to expand our feeling inside our body, our inspiration, our joy, we can then become more expansive than the level of consciousness we were holding when we perceived the issue as a problem, concern, or hurdle in our lives. This doesn’t mean we don’t need to address the issue, but when we expand our level of awareness all of a sudden what we once perceived as a problem is now a simple pebble in the middle of the road we simply need to step over. 

Follow @DavidSamuelStraus  for more daily wisdom!

node.text:
Do you know what your ego mind is manifesting? We are powerful manifestors. Always. There is no time in life that we don’t manifest what is important to us. You might say, wait, I didn't manifest this or that in my life?! But you did. And that’s okay. You see, we always manifest things that are important to us. If we have a lot of anger, frustration, or sadness, we will manifest that into our lives. You might say, you don’t want to manifest that or that these things aren’t important to you, and that would be true. But it may not be true for your ego-mind👾

When you have conflict in your life, look at your ego mind. What is going on there? What might your ego mind be manifesting? If you look at that honestly and you find you have a belief around it that you need, want, or think you deserve it in your life on some level, then put it into your Silent Watcher.
The Silent Watcher is your place to go to dissolve those beliefs. The Silent Watcher is a place without judgement. In your neutral observer, you will be able to drop your ego’s chatter and watch your life from a new perspective. It works every time. Have you tried it yet?🤩

Be happy, be abundant, be in your highest and best life always.✨

Follow @deirdre.hade for more!

Imagine a problem, a concern, or hurdle you currently have in your life.  That problem concern or hurdle is equal to your current level of awareness (consciousness) as it relates to that problem.  When we know how to expand our feeling inside our body, our inspiration, our joy, we can then become more expansive than the level of consciousness we were holding when we perceived the issue as a problem, concern, or hurdle in our lives. This doesn’t mean we don’t need to address the issue, but when we expand our level of awareness all of a sudden what we once perceived as a problem is now a simple pebble in the middle of the road we simply need to step over.

I want you to consider answering this question: What difference do I want to make on the planet before I leave? How do I want the world to be better before I leave? How do I want my relationships, my neighborhood, anything I encounter to be better before I leave? As you are answering that question, you are beginning to bump into the reason why you chose this incarnation. Are you feeling it with me right now? What difference do you want to make before you leave this planet? Remember you're feeling into what difference do I want to make before I leave this planet as your asking that question, allow for a wonderful goal to emerge. It doesn't have to be far-flung right now. It doesn't have to be world-shaking and way out there. It can be a baby step. It could be something small in the beginning, but it's attached to the difference you want to make on the planet. So you're asking yourself, what difference do I want to make before I leave this planet?
Mentally begin to describe that goal. You don't have to ask, how am I going to do the goal? Just describe it for if you know what you'll ultimately know how, if you know the, what you're always know the how, what is the goal articulated to yourself? How does it feel? What difference do I want to make before I leave the planet? What goal is worthy of that? Describe it to yourself. And what does it feel like?
Now, remember you are a radiant being, and something wants to emerge, feel into that, and then be aware that from this moment on, as you ask that pertinent question, what difference do I want to make? You will be inspired by these questions and thoughts will begin to emerge within you that you're not generating, but you are obtaining from the mind of the infinite.
You are obtaining thoughts from the mind at the infinite, based on the question you're living in. So what's going on here. You're not a victim. You're not a victim to circumstances and situations and conditions. You are a radiant being that has dominion over their attention and is catching a goal worthy of you making the difference. You have come here to make.
Share your experience in the comments below!    Follo

node.text:
The word consciousness is thrown about so casually that it’s easy to lose sight of what it means, even more so when it is defined as being “awakened.” Awakened consciousness is a state of being aware that you are aware. It is a realization that you are the watcher, the witness within you—not the analyzer, not the thinker, not even the meditator, but that which is the impartial witness of every aspect of your being & doing.

When you consciously realize that you are the watcher, you are freed from the narrow confines of outer labels: male, female, Asian, Caucasian, Black, gay, straight, vegetarian, carnivore, Republican, Democrat, Christian, Hindu, Taoist, & so on. These must crumble for your true identity as pure consciousness to emerge. Beliefs, concepts, and perceptions are the contents of consciousness, but they are not consciousness itself. We know they are not consciousness because they can be changed, shifted, transformed. Consciousness itself is an “isness” that is the changeless, formless, ever-existing aspect of your being that is not influenced by anything external. What is vital to your spiritual understanding is that you are empowered to evolve the contents of your consciousness into alignment with consciousness itself. As you do so, the contents of your consciousness change their vibratory frequency, causing a resultant shift in the outer circumstances of your life.

Let us all become lionhearted spiritual warriors knowing that we may apply our soulware of happiness and uplift ourselves and all beings right on the ground where we now stand.  Follow @michaelbbeckwith for more spiritual wisdom! 🌟

It sounds so crazy that a simple sketch of another person could really change someone's life forever.  But the reality is that it has and could do the same for you.
 
Do you wonder what your Soulmate looks like? Click the link in @awakeningpeople profile to receive your sketch.
 
Maybe, your sketch will turn out to exactly the person you are in a relationship with right now.  If that's the case, then he's definitely the one for you.  But what if it brings back a totally different person? 
 
And if you are single and curious to know where to look for your soulmate, our sketches not only give you a drawing but a timeframe and where you might actually meet this Soulmate.
 
So don't delay, because each day is an opportunity to find your Soulmate that can pass you by. Simply click the link in @awakeningpeople profile to receive your sketch.

You, as an emanation of The Presence, have more power than you can even imagine. You have soul faculties that have yet to be activated and powers that have yet to be expressed. The Presence of God has entrusted you with all the qualities and attributes that are within the matrix of God Itself. This trust comes with a mandate that you become an alchemist of your own life even while having a human incarnation.

Down through the ages, we have come to know an alchemist as one who can turn lead into gold. Spiritually, we know that we have the potential to turn the leaden places in our life experiences into golden opportunities and glowing possibilities. An alchemist knows that to turn lead into gold, you must have a small piece of gold as a part of the process. You must have the frequency of gold (however small) to quicken the lead to rise to a higher frequency.

This analogy brings us to the awareness that in order to be the alchemists of our own lives, we must embrace the frequency of the quality we want to bring into our life to activate those leaden places, so to speak. We must find skillful means to touch the vibration of what we are seeking and change the vibration of the harsh realities we may be facing. Everything is vibration!

As Alchemists, we practice shifting the vibrations appearing as obstacles, hindrances, and problems into the higher frequencies of opportunities, possibilities, and real revelations of wholeness. You are more powerful than you think.

Become the alchemist of your life! ⚗️ 

Follow @michaelbbeckwith for more!

"When the student is ready the teacher will appear, but when the student is truly ready the teacher will disappear."

I want to be clear and make sure I provide context for this post, which I build upon in the full podcast interview. This understanding described in this clip has come with the context of working with over 20 different spiritual leaders in my lifetime. I still have people I learn from but I know a human can only take me so far & can not explain the explainable, which is Source/ God/ The Universe. The difference for me now is I now know there is nothing any human has that I don't. There is nothing they have access to that I don't. Therefore, we are equal.

It took me much pain to get to this understanding, but it was all worth it because it made me wise. It gave me strength beyond comprehension and it forced me not to trust humans but to trust my own heart. My own master within.

At the end of the day, that is really the only thing we can truly rely on. Our greatest teacher is us. We are what we are seeking, it's all inside, and my current level of understanding is that the spiritual journey is less about becoming and actually just returning to the essence we came to this world with. We get there by surrendering to who we think we are and moving closer to grace... Here's the thing though, you can not get there as your identity... your job, etc... You have to move beyond all those layers and then you will arrive at the true you. This takes time, practice and the proper tools to get there, but it's all there for you :)

If you're reading this... stop putting people on peddle stools, stop thinking others have answers that you do not, own your power as a sovereign human, and just show up as you. That is perfect enough. 

👉Follow @antonwisbiski for more wisdom!

And if you are single and curious to know where to look for your soulmate, our sketches not only give you a drawing but a timeframe and where you might actually meet this Soulmate.
 
So don't delay, because each day is an opportunity to find your Soulmate that can pass you by. Simply click the link in @awakeningpeople profile to receive your sketch.
